overview: The Avro Vulcan is a jet-powered delta wing strategic bomber, which was operated by the Royal Air Force (RAF) from 1956 until 1984. Experience the grace and beauty of this majestic aircraft from its early years to the current 603 s re-build at its birthplace - AVRO, Woodford. With some never before seen vintage footage, together with current footage of the 603 s restoration and interviews with ex-crew members, this video explores the Vulcan's pedigree and illustrious career. The Spirit of Woodford is very much alive!
title: Vulcan: Spirit of Woodford
